@G[c3 stills_71.png]@L
		@H Historical Background @L
		Capua was founded around 600 BC, and the original settlement was established by the Etruscans at the height of their power. Capua's name in the Etruscan language, "Capeva" meant "city of marshes". A Samnite invasion in the year 424 BC led to Capua being occupied and broken free from its Etruscan ties. @L@L
		Rome had been at war with the Samnites and various other affiliated tribes in central Italy during a period known as the Samnite Wars. Samnites were a very warlike Italic people who lived in south-central Italy. Some cities have been recognized as Roman allies, even being granted citizenship in certain cases. These events demonstrated that Rome was a significant regional power capable of protecting its allies. The independent city of Capua found the possibility of renewed Samnite aggression most troubling. @L@L Accordingly, the Roman Senate had extended diplomatic overtures to Capua to make them a Roman ally. In the year 343 BC, Capua accepted the terms, regarding themselves as more closely aligned with the Latins than the Samnites. This was certain to increase tensions in the area, but Rome was confident in her military prowess and that the economic benefits from controlling Capua outweighed the risks.@L@L

		@G[c3 instructions icon.png]
		@H Instructions @L
		Governor, take charge of the local area and develop it into a true regional trade hub and economic powerhouse. Due to our mighty legions, you do not need to worry about city defenses; and even with Samnite aggression being so high, it's unlikely they will invade Capua directly. Instead, your city will support our @war @effort and I will often demand shipments of wheat and weapons to be sent to our legions. @L@L
		The land near Capua does not have deposits of suitable stone or marble so you will need to import these if you want to build larger civic projects. On the bright side, the land around Capua is quite fertile, so you can expect easy cultivation of @vines, @olives, and other @foodstuffs. The only challenge will be in logistics, transporting goods and provisions from the farmlands to your marketplaces in a timely fashion. A wise governor should make good use the of the sturdy local oxen to arrange transport via @cart @depots.@L@L
		Locals are also very fond of ludi, or games. You will be tasked with carefully managing the entertainment venues in Capua. @L@L
		Even though there are difficulties awaiting you in Capua, I expect a relatively high level of overall prosperity to be achieved. @L@L
