		@H Historical Background @L
		Capua was a very important major city for most of Rome's history. For example, during the Second Punic War, it was able to raise and equip 30000 infantry and 4000 cavalry by its own to contribute to the war. In terms of economy, Capua was famed for its grain production as well as its manufacturing of various bronze objects of which both the elder Cato and the elder Pliny spoke highly of in terms of quality. @L@L@L@L@L

